Title: Learning with a Sparse Distributed Memory  
Author: Jim Marshall Lisa Meeden 
Date: 1 May 1989  
Address: Bloomington, Indiana  
Affiliation: Computer Science Department Indiana University  
Abstract: In this paper we describe a software implementation of a sparse distributed memory in the *Lisp language on a Connection Machine. We use several different learning tasks to evaluate the performance of the memory model, including generalization, prediction, and retraining. 
